This system should use production rules (IF–THEN rules) to control devices like:

Lights

Thermostat

Security system

Doors

Curtains

Sprinklers

Heating/Cooling

PRODUCTION RULES
Lighting Rules
RULE L1:
IF motion detected in the bedroom AND it's nighttime
THEN turn on the bedroom lights.

RULE L2:
IF no motion detected for 10 minutes
THEN turn off the lights.

RULE L3:
IF sunlight intensity is high
THEN close smart curtains halfway.

 Temperature / AC Rules
RULE T1:
IF temperature > 28°C
THEN turn on the air conditioner.

RULE T2:
IF temperature < 20°C
THEN turn on the heater.

RULE T3:
IF no one is home
THEN set thermostat to energy-saving mode.

  Security Rules
RULE S1:
IF all occupants leave the house
THEN activate security alarm.

RULE S2:
IF window is opened after 11 pm AND no motion detected inside
THEN send security alert to phone.

RULE S3:
IF unknown face detected at the door
THEN lock all smart doors.

 Garden / Outdoor Rules
RULE G1:
IF soil moisture is low AND rainfall probability < 20%
THEN turn on sprinklers.

RULE G2:
IF wind speed > 50 km/h
THEN close all outdoor awnings.

A smart home has:

Inputs (Facts)

Time (day/night)

Temperature

Motion detection

Light level

Weather data

Security status

Door/window sensors

Knowledge Base (Rules)

All the IF–THEN rules you write.

Inference Engine

The system checks which rules are true and activates the actions.
